      "writtenOn": "2020-10-26T19:49:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Implementing page token right now is hard, since datastore.RunMulti doesn\u0027t support cursors. I was considering to later add a request field \"page_size\" with semantics of \"if 0 or missing - try to fetch everything\". Then page_token can be added in a backward compatible way (old clients will just keep timing out when trying to fetch everything).\n\nI\u0027m afraid that if I add noop page_token right now, then:\n1. It will be ignored.\n2. If it\u0027s not ignored, it is more unused code to implement and test on the client.\n\nI\u0027ll think more about it.",
